1 adopted working budget for final approval.
2 (2) A superintendent shall not propose and a local board of education shall not adopt
3 a draft, tentative, or working budget that does not include a minimum reserve of
4 at least two percent (2%) of the total budget.
5 Section 2. KRS 160.431 is amended to read as follows:
6 (1) The local district superintendent shall appoint a finance officer who shall be
7 responsible for the cash, investment, and financial management of the school
8 district.
9 (2) (a) A person initially employed as a school finance officer on or after July 1,
10 2015, shall obtain certification from the Department of Education prior to
11 holding the position and entering the duties of the position of school finance
12 officer.
13 (b) The Kentucky Board of Education shall promulgate administrative regulations
14 to prescribe the criteria and procedures to be used in the certification process
15 for a school finance officer.
16 (c) The administrative regulations promulgated under this subsection shall
17 specify:
18 1. The initial qualification requirements for school finance officer
19 certification;
20 2. The certification application and appeal process; and
21 3. The certification renewal process.
22 (3) The school finance officer shall be required to complete forty-two (42) hours of
23 continuing education every two (2) years from a provider approved by the
24 Department of Education. The Kentucky Board of Education shall promulgate
25 administrative regulations to identify and prescribe the criteria for fulfilling the
26 requirements of this subsection. The administrative regulations shall specify:
27 (a) The topics of continuing education;
Page 3 of 19
SB000310.100 - 1799 - XXXX 2/2/2026 4:46 PM GA

UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS SB 3/GA
1 (b) Qualifications for continuing education providers;
2 (c) Consequences for failure to meet the continuing education requirement; and
3 (d) Requirements for reinstatement of school finance officer certification.
4 (4) (a) The finance officer shall present a detailed monthly financial report for board
5 approval to include the previous month's revenues and expenditures of the
6 district. The monthly report shall be posted on the district's Web site for a
7 minimum of six (6) months after its approval.
8 (b) Within six (6) months following the end of each fiscal year, the finance
9 officer shall submit to the Kentucky Department of Education a detailed
10 annual financial report to include the district's total assets, liabilities,
11 revenues, and expenditures. The annual report shall be posted on the district's
12 financial disclosure website required in Section 3 of this Act[Web site] and
13 department's website[Web site] for a minimum of two (2) years.
14 (c) 1. The Department of Education shall review each district's annual
15 financial report and shall provide, within two (2) months of receipt, the
16 local board of education a written report indicating the financial status
17 of the district. The department's written report shall be posted on the
18 department's website[Web site] and the district financial disclosure
19 website required in Section 3 of this Act[district's Web site] for a
20 minimum of two (2) years.
21 2. The commissioner of education shall annually present to the Interim
22 Joint Committee on Education a copy of the department's written report
23 for each district.
24 (d) Nothing in this subsection shall lessen the obligation of a school district to
25 publish its financial statements in accordance with KRS 160.463.
