3 Section 4. KRS 157.440 is amended to read as follows:
4 (1) (a) Notwithstanding any statutory provisions to the contrary, effective for school
5 years beginning after July 1, 1990, the board of education of each school
6 district may levy an equivalent tax rate as defined in[ subsection (9)(a) of]
7 KRS 160.470(8)(a) which will produce up to fifteen percent (15%) of those
8 revenues guaranteed by the program to support education excellence in
9 Kentucky. The levy for the 1990-91 school year shall be made no later than
10 October 1, 1989, and no later than October 1, 1990, for the 1991-92 school
11 year, and by October 1 of each odd-numbered year thereafter. Effective with
12 the 1990-91 school year, revenue generated by this levy shall be equalized at
13 one hundred fifty percent (150%) of the statewide average per pupil
14 assessment.
15 (b) To participate in the Facilities Support Program of Kentucky, the board of
16 education of each school district shall commit at least an equivalent tax rate of
17 five cents ($0.05) to debt service, new facilities, or major renovations of
18 existing school facilities, or the purchase of land if approved by the
19 commissioner of education as provided in KRS 157.420(4)(b). The five cents
20 ($0.05) shall be in addition to the thirty cents ($0.30) required by KRS
21 160.470(8)[(9)] and any levy pursuant to paragraph (a) of this subsection. The
22 levy shall be made no later than October 1 of each odd-numbered year.
23 Eligibility for equalization funds for the biennium shall be based on the
24 district funds committed to debt service on that date. The five cents ($0.05)
25 shall be equalized at one hundred fifty percent (150%) of the statewide
26 average per pupil assessment. The equalization funds shall be committed to
27 debt service to the greatest extent possible, but any excess equalization funds
