16 Section 9. KRS 160.530 is amended to read as follows:
17 The money collected by taxation under the provisions of KRS 160.460 to 160.520 and
18 other school money shall be expended by the board of education in accordance with the
19 working[recommendations contained in the] budget submitted to and approved by the
20 Kentucky Board of Education.
21 Section 10. KRS 160.550 is amended to read as follows:
22 (1) No superintendent shall recommend and no board member shall knowingly vote for
23 an expenditure in excess of the income and revenue of any year, as shown by the
24 working budget adopted by the board and approved by the Kentucky Board of
25 Education, except for a purpose for which bonds have been voted or in case of an
26 emergency declared by the Kentucky Board of Education.
27 (2) Any school district having authorized an expenditure in violation of subsection (1)
Page 17 of 19
SB000310.100 - 1799 - XXXX 2/2/2026 4:46 PM GA

UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS SB 3/GA
1 of this section may be so certified at any time by the Kentucky Board of Education.
2 A district so certified shall thereafter, any contrary statutory provisions
3 notwithstanding, make no expenditure of money, give no authorization involving
4 the expenditure of money, and make no employment, purchase, or contract, unless
5 the chief state school officer has approved in writing, as fiscally sound and
6 necessary, the expenditure, authorization, employment, purchase, or contract. Any
7 expenditure, authorization, employment, purchase, or contract made in violation of
8 this subsection shall be void.
9 (3) Any school district subject to the provisions of subsection (2) of this section shall so
10 remain until such time as the Kentucky Board of Education has approved, in
11 conformity with Section 1 of this Act[KRS 160.470], a working budget for the
12 district for a succeeding fiscal year.
13 (4) In addition to the penalties set forth in KRS 160.990, any person who knowingly
14 expends or authorizes the expenditure of school district funds or who knowingly
15 authorizes or executes any employment, purchase, or contract, in violation of this
16 section, shall be jointly and severably liable in person and upon any official bond he
17 has given to such district to the extent of any payments on the void claim. For
18 purposes of this section, "knowingly" shall mean a person acts with respect to
19 conduct or to a circumstance described by a statute defining an offense when he is
20 aware that his conduct is of that nature or that the circumstance exists.
21 Section 11. KRS 424.250 is amended to read as follows:
22 At the same time that copies of the budget of a school district are filed with the clerk of
23 the tax levying authority for the district, as provided in Section 1 of this Act[KRS
24 160.470], the board of education of the district shall cause the budget to be advertised for
25 the district by publishing a copy of the budget in a newspaper and on the district's
26 website.
27 Section 12. Upon the effective date of this Act, the school board of each school
